                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person39" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             called on his recognizance, and not appearing, his recognizance was ordered to be estreated.</p>

               <p>Mr. Jacques. My lord, before the case is opened I trust you will permit me to have the witnesses sent out of Court; and there is another circumstance which is unusual, that they may be sent with an officer, and no person be permitted to speak to them or give them papers.</p>

               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="179007100003"></xptr>Mr. Garrow. It is very proper on both sides, all the witnesses.</p>

               <p>The indictment opened by Mr. Garrow.</p>

               <p>My lord and gentlemen of the jury. This is an indictment against 
               <persName id="t17900710-1-person40">
                  Robert
                   Jacques
               <interp inst="t17900710-1-person40" type="surname" value="Jacques"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person40" type="given" value="Robert"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person40" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , 
               <persName id="t17900710-1-person41">
                  John
                   Tronson
               <interp inst="t17900710-1-person41" type="surname" value="Tronson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person41" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person41" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             otherwise James Smith, 
               <persName id="t17900710-1-person42">
                  Richard
                   Bailey
               <interp inst="t17900710-1-person42" type="surname" value="Bailey"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person42" type="given" value="Richard"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person42" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
