                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person107" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , in order that judgments might be entered up, and executions taken out thereon against this declarant, on which he was to be removed to the Fleet, and that he should be enabled to make his escape from thence, in order to fix the warden of the said prison with the amount of the said debts, and that he should have part of the money to be received from the said warden in consequence of the said escape; and faith, that he having so agreed, he did accordingly sign the said warrants of attorney for the said pretended debts; although he positively faith, he never in his life saw either the said 
               <persName id="t17900710-1-person108">
                  Edmund
                   Alder
               <interp inst="t17900710-1-person108" type="surname" value="Alder"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person108" type="given" value="Edmund"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17900710-1-person108" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             and 
               <persName id="t17900710-1-person109">
                  Richard
                   Bailey
               <interp inst="t17900710-1-person109" type="surname" value="Bailey"></interp>
